# Implementation Workflow

## Standard Cycle

### 1. Plan
- Pick route pattern: **A** (auth: routes → feature) or **B** (page composes features/admin queries)
- Read affected layers per `frontend-layering.mdc`
- Note IAM implications (auth, tokens, OIDC redirect, MFA/WebAuthn)

### 2. Implement
- Auth screen → feature in `src/features/` + wire in `routes/index.tsx` with `AuthLayout`
- Console/settings screen → page in `src/pages/` + admin hooks in `features/admin/` if needed
- New routes: `src/routes/index.tsx` + guards; console nav in `console-nav.ts` if applicable
- New API calls: `src/api/client.ts` + types in `src/api/types.ts`

### 3. Test
- Manual flow in browser with backend running on `:3000`
- Run `make lint` and `make build` (TypeScript + Vite)

### 4. Backend alignment
- Env vars: update `.env.example` and note matching backend vars in README
- OIDC/WebAuthn: align `OIDC_LOGIN_PAGE_URL`, `WEBAUTHN_RP_ORIGINS` on backend
- API shape changes: update `src/api/types.ts`; optional `make generate-api`

### 5. Review & Integrate
- Self-review diff; `make check`
- Conventional commit; PR with test plan

## Bug Fix Workflow
1. Reproduce in browser (note route, network tab, console)
2. Root cause — don't patch symptoms
3. Minimal fix at correct layer (auth vs api vs feature vs route guard)
4. `make lint` and `make build`
5. Verify against backend if API-related

## Local Dev Commands
```bash
make setup      # .env + npm install
make run        # Vite dev server :5173 (proxies API to :3000)
make lint       # ESLint
make build      # tsc + vite build
make check      # lint + build
```
